review_blob: 33 cl can from Mas supermarket. Porurs golden clear with a white head. Aromas of malts. Sweet taste. Nice in the spanish sun.
33 cl can from Mas supermarket. Enjoyed (not so much) straight from the can. Watery and tasteless stuff. Avoid.
33 cl bottle from Mas supermarket. Pours hazy orange with a white head. Aromas of hops and citrus. Bitter taste. Good beer.
33 cl bottle from shop in Nerja. Porus hazy golden with a white head. Aromas of hops and malt. Taste is bitter. Refreshing in the spanish sun.
33 cl bottle from shop i Nerja. Pours golden clear with a nice white head. Aromas of grains and malt. Taste is bittersweet. Good beer.
2 litre growler shared. Pours amber clear with a big white head. Aromas of hops and fruits. Taste is bitter. Good grocery-strenght IPA.
Bottle shared with Kristian. Pours almost pitch black with a small beige head. Aromas of whisky, coffee and licorice. Taste is bittersweet. Good stuff.
50 cl can from Rema 1000 supermarket. Pours pale golden clear with a small white head. Aromas of malts and hops. Pretty ordinary lager. Sweet taste.
33 cl bottle from Vinmonopolet. Pours pitch black with a beige head. Aromas of coffee, malts, chocolate and dark syrup. Taste is bittersweet. Really good stuff.
beer_name: Anchor Argonaut Collection: Flying Cloud San Francisco Stout

review_blob: 50 cl bottle from Vinmonopolet. Pours clear golden with a big white head. Aromas of malt, dirt, metal and herbs. Taste is bitter with hints of sourness. Good beer.
33 cl bottle from Polet. Pours cloudy pale yellow with no head. Aromas of honey and citrus. Taste is sweet and sour. Interesting brew.
50 cl can from Coop Extra supermarket. 4.7 abv version. Pours clear goldeb with a nice white head. Aromas of caramel and malts. Taste is sweet. Refreshing brew.
50 cl can from Coop Extra supermarket. Pours hazy pale yellow with a soon fading white head. Aromas of hops, yeast and citrusy fruits. Taste is bitter. Good beer from macro brewer Hansa.
33 cl bottle from Beard and Burger Grill in Albir Spain. Pours hazy pale golden with almost no head. Aromas of yeast and spices. Taste is bitter with a sweetnsour finish. Good beer.
33 cl bottle from Consum supermarket Albir Spain. Enjoyed straight from bottle. Aromas of toasted malts. Taste is bitter. Good crisp lager with a bite.
33 cl bottle from Copa Ropa in Albir Spain. Pours hazy brown with a small beige head. Aromas of malts, caramel and spices. Taste is bitter with a sweet ending. Another good brew from Tyris.
33 cl bottle from Copa Ropa in Albir Spain. Pours hazy brownish with a big beige head. Aromas of malts and fruits. Taste is bittersweet. Reminds me of an norwegian bayer. Good.
33 cl bottle from CopaRopa in lAlbir Spain. Pours hazy copper with a small white head. Aromas of fruits and hops. Taste is bitter with a sweet tone. Good IPA.
33 cl bottle from Consum supermarket in lAlbir Spain. Pours clear pale golden with a small white head. Grassy and malty aroma. Taste is bittersweet. Nice in sunny Spain.
33 cl bottle from Consum supermarket in Costa Blanca Spain. Pours clear golden with a fine white head. Aromas of hops and fresh cut grass. Taste is bitter. Good pilsner.
33 cl bottle from CopaRopa. Pours cloudy brown with a small off-white head. Aromas of malts, caramel and yeast. Taste is bittersweet. Good.
33 cl bottle from CopaRopa. Pours hazy orange with almost no head. Aromas of hops and citrus. Taste is medium bitter. Nice beer.
33 cl bottle from CopaRopa. Pours almost pitch black with a creamy brown head. Aromas of roasted coffee, malts, licorice and smoke. Taste is bittersweet. Good and smooth beer.
33 cl bottle from CopaRopa. Pours hazy orange with a small white head. Aromas and hops and citrus fruits. Nice brew.
beer_name: Tyris Au Yeah! American Pale Ale

review_blob: 33 cl bottle from CopaRopa. Pours hazy pale yellow with a small head. Light in taste and aromas. Refreshing.
50 cl can from Coop Extra. Pours clear amber with a small head. Aromas of malt and caramel. Taste is bittersweet. OK lite beer.
50 cl can from Rema 1000. Pours clear golden with a small white head. Aromas of malt. Taste is bittersweet with metallic aftertaste. Watery and thin pale lager.

200 cl growler from the brewery. Pours clear dark golden with a big off-white head. Aromas of citrus, hops and spices. Taste is bitter. Medium carbonation. Refreshing and crisp. Cool concept at the brewery - bring your empty growler and get it refilled.

75 cl bottle from Vinmonopolet. Pours clear pale golden with a big lasting white head. Aromas of hops, citrus fruits and yeast. Taste is bitersweet with a dry finish. Great looking bottle with white wax over the cap.
33 cl bottle from Meny supermarket. Pours cloudy pale yellow with a big frothy head. Aromas of malts and fruits. Taste is light bitter with a dry finish. Crisp and well made pilsner.
33 cl bottle from Meny supermarket. Pours almost pitch black with a huge head. Aromas of roasted malt, coffee, licorice and more roasted malt... Taste is bitter with dry finish. Good stout!
33 cl bottle from Meny supermarket. Pours hazy orange with a small white head. Aromas of hops and fruits. Taste is bitter. Cant say I miss the gluten...
33 cl bottle from Meny supermarket. Pours hazy orange with a small white head. Aromas of hops and earth. Taste is bitter. Pricey but nice.
beer_name: Kolonihagen India Pale Ale Dry Hop Cascade   (4,7%)

review_blob: 33 cl bottle from Meny supermarket. Pours hazy yellow with a small soon fading white head. Aromas of yeast, grass and fruits. Taste is bittersweet. Refreshing summers beer from Lervig.
50 cl can from Rema 1000. Pours golden clear with a small white head. Aromas of coriander, herbs, orange, yeast and wheat. Taste is sweet with bitter finish. Not very Belgian in style but OK I guess.
50 cl bottle from Vinmonopolet. Pours clear amber with a big off-white head. Aromas of malts, fruits and yeast. Taste is bittersweet. Good dunkelweizen.
50 cl bottle from Coop Extra. Pours hazy red-ish with a big white head. Aromas of citrusy hops. Taste is bitter. Mighty fine IPA.
33 cl bottle from Rema 1000. Pours golden clear with a small white head. Aromas of lemon (!) and citrus. Taste is sweet. I guess this one is better suited in July than in February.
33 cl bottle from Vinmonopolet. Pours dark brown with a small beige head. Aromas of roasted coffee, malt and chocolate. Taste is sweet with alcoholic finish. Decent brew.
33 cl bottle from Coop Extra. Pours hazy dark golden with a small white head. Aromas of malt, caramel and butter. Taste is bittersweet. Alright.
33 cl bottle from Vinmonopolet. Pours cloudy yellow with a small white head. Aromas of yeast, banana and grass. Taste is sweet with alcoholic finish. Good tripel.
33 cl bottle from Vinmonopolet. Pours hazy golden with a big soon fading head. Aromas of fruits and berries but a bit artificial. Taste is bitter and sour. Strange IPA. More like a sour beer.
50 cl bottle from Coop Extra. Pours hazy yellow with a big white head. Aromas of citrus and hops. Taste is bitter. Really enjoyable.
50 cl bottle from Rema 1000 rdalstangen. Pours hazy orange with a big white head. Aromas of wheat, yeast and banana. Taste is sweet and sour. Decent hefeweizen.
50 cl bottle from Joker Gudvangen. Pours almost pitch black with no head. Aromas of coffee, licorice and malt. Taste is bittersweet. Good stout from Tya.
33 cl bottle from Joker Gudvangen. Pours hazy brownish with no head. Aromas of malt with hints of caramel. Taste is bittersweet. Average.
33 cl bottle from Coop Extra. Pours hazy pale yellow with a big white head. Aromas of weat, yeast, spices and hay. Taste is bitter. Good wit.
33 cl bottle from Coop Extra. Pours hazy orange with a small white head. Aromas of hops and citrus. Taste is bitter. Good beer.
50 cl bottle from Rema 1000. Pours hazy orange with a small white head. Aromas of hops, flowers and hay. Taste is bitter. Low carbonation. Beautiful label. Nice brew.
50 cl bottle from Rema 1000 rdalstangen. Pours hazy brown with a big white head. Aromas of wheat, yeast, flowers, hops and hay. Taste is bitter. Fine beer from Sogn.
